I'm open to other solutions for fixing this. Using AtomicBoolean in the most basic way would end up being more costly:
```
    @Override
    public boolean isDestroyed() {
      entryIsDestroyed.compareAndSet(false,
          isThisRegionBeingClosedOrDestroyed() || LocalRegion.this.basicGetEntry(key) == null);
      return entryIsDestroyed.get();
    }
```
Here's the original code. I made the boolean entryIsDestroyed volatile which isn't perfect but it is better than what's on develop. I could leave it alone but I'm pretty sure it's not really correct:
```
    @Override
    public boolean isDestroyed() {
      if (entryIsDestroyed) {
        return true;
      }
      if (isThisRegionBeingClosedOrDestroyed() || LocalRegion.this.basicGetEntry(key) == null) {
        entryIsDestroyed = true;
      }
      return entryIsDestroyed;
    }
```

@dickcav Thanks for catching the LICENSE file update. Looks like we need to update top-level file if we include any dependency into *src* distribution otherwise we update `geode-assembly/src/main/dist/LICENSE` file.
I have corrected the LICENSE changes and moved those into assembly LICENSE file.

Also, I have reverted NOTICE file changes as I still have more work to do, so will create a new PR.
